article.headline: VMI 72, Army 63
article.story:
WEST POINT, N.Y. (AP) -- Chavis Holmes scored 20 points to lead
VMI to a 72-63 win over Army Thursday night.

Reggie Williams scored nine of his 15 points on free throws in
the game's final seven minutes to help the Keydets (3-4) hold off
the Black Knights (3-5).

Army was 3-of-26 from the field in the first half as VMI built a
33-12 halftime lead.

Matt Bell scored eight of his 28 points for the Black Knights
during a 12-3 run to open the second half. Army cut the deficit to
eight twice but could get no closer. Dan Borcherdt contributed 12
points.

Travis Holmes added 10 points for the Keydets.
